  "prompt": "How do I stop comparing myself with others? I am getting frustrated & losing my confidence everyday. What's the solution?",
  "response": "Here are some effective strategies to stop comparing yourself to others:\n\n1. Self-awareness\n- Recognize when you're comparing yourself\n- Understand that comparisons are often unrealistic\n- Acknowledge your own unique journey\n\n2. Focus on personal growth\n- Set personal goals\n- Track your own progress\n- Compete with yourself, not others\n- Celebrate your own achievements\n\n3. Practice gratitude\n- Appreciate what you have\n- Keep a gratitude journal\n- Recognize your own strengths\n- Shift focus from what's missing to what's present\n\n4. Limit social media exposure\n- Reduce time on platforms that trigger comparisons\n- Unfollow accounts that make you feel inadequate\n- Curate a positive digital environment\n\n5. Develop self-confidence\n- Practice positive self-talk\n- Build skills and knowledge\n- Take care of physical and mental health\n- Accept yourself unconditionally\n\n6. Reframe perspective\n- Everyone's journey is different\n- Success isn't linear\n- Failures are learning opportunities\n- Understand that external appearances are often misleading\n\n7. Seek professional help\n- Consider counseling\n- Learn coping mechanisms\n- Address underlying self-esteem issues\n\nRemember: Your worth isn't determined by comparing yourself to others. You are unique and valuable.",
